title: Southwestern Breakfast Slow Cooker Casserole
directions: In a large bowl, whisk together first seven ingredients. Stir in beans, corn, ham, cheese and chilies. Stir in bread to moisten. Transfer to a 5-qt. slow cooker coated with cooking spray.
Cook, covered, on low until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean, 2-1/2 to 3-1/2 hours. Let stand, uncovered, 10 minutes before serving. If desired, serve with pico de gallo.
ingredients: 1 can (15 ounces) black beans, rinsed and drained
1 can (4 ounces) chopped green chilies, drained
6 slices whole wheat bread, lightly toasted and cubed
